      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hyde Park and Wicker Park are considered \"safe\" areas, but they're not exactly the most affluent neighborhoods, and you'll likely encounter a lot of students and artists who are, shall we say, less polished. That being said, if you're looking for areas to avoid, you might want to steer clear of Englewood, which is a high-crime area with a lot of gang activity. You might also want to avoid the West Garfield Park area at night, as it's been plagued by crime and poverty. And of course, there's always the South Side, which is generally considered to be a bit rougher around the edges. But hey, if you're looking for a real adventure, you could always stay in one of the many sketchy hotels in the Loop and explore the city on your own. Just don't say I didn't warn you.",
